comments.body:
Sorry for not replying to this thread earlier.

@rknop if you want that I try to offer you a solution for your problem based on `--gidmap`, I would need the output of the command: `podman unshare cat /proc/self/gid_map`, as @giuseppe was asking you earlier. It is possible, albeit a bit convoluted. You can find a step by step example at https://rocker-project.org/use/rootless.html#ask-the-system-administrator-to-subordinate-the-group that may be of help to you.

And with #18713, if everything goes well and it gets merged, you will just need `podman run --gidmap "+g1000:@5555" ...` to get GID 5555 mapped to group 1000.
